PN,35302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F353A1772467872
OL,3,CSustainable clothing event in Penrith
OL,4,Chopes to reduce landfill
OL,6,FThe Founding Director of Cumbria
OL,7,FClothing Collective, Gail Gravett,
OL,8,Fexplains the shocking stats around why
OL,9,Fthe organisation started: "There is a
OL,10,Fmountain of clothing that you can see
OL,11,Fin the Atacama Desert from space. We
OL,12,Fnow can see the same problems
OL,13,Fhappening in Ghana."
OL,15,FMs Gravett says Cumbria ships 76% of
OL,16,Fits clothing waste to the Global
OL,17,FSouth, where it's ending up in the
OL,18,Flandfills and in the rivers.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G2/6
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,354,350,120,260,000,100
PN,35303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F353A1772467872
OL,3,CSustainable clothing event in Penrith
OL,4,Chopes to reduce landfill
OL,6,FShe said: "There is enough clothes in
OL,7,Fthe world today to clothe the next six
OL,8,Fgenerations of people. That's without
OL,9,Fus buying anything.
OL,11,F"On average, women only wear 28% of
OL,12,Fwhat's in our clothing, and they're
OL,13,Factually saying that this year they're
OL,14,Fgoing to be producing 20 billion items
OL,15,Fof new clothing, and there's only 7
OL,16,Fbillion people in the world."
OL,18,FThe organisation says something has to
OL,19,Fchange because textile production uses
OL,20,Foil and depleting resources.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G3/6
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
